text: I love the plot, I love the characters, but I still hate this movie, let alone the red band trailer. The trailer was supposed to make people want to see the movie. But due to all of it's raunchy humor, it did the opposite effect for me and the other critics. Its' jokes were just like the Cave Fraggles' jokes; anti humor. For example, bisexual puppet prostitutes. OK, what's the joke? The trailer also makes the main character Phil Phillips look like a jerk when really he is just this character who is tough on the outside, but a big softie on the inside. This movie also ruins a lot of reputations. It ruins the Muppets' reputation because they're supposed to be family-friendly but people keep calling the characters in the movie "Muppets." It also ruins Sesame Street's reputation because it's supposed to be for kids but the tagline, "No Sesame. All Street." makes it look like Sesame Street was associated with this movie. Todd Berger seriously must've been high when writing this movie putting a bad combination of Muppet like puppets and adult humor. You'd think those characters would look friendly when you first see them. First Brian Henson fires Steve Whitmire, and now he does this crap. Jim Henson would not approve of this at all.
